from the great Connor Mead?

02:38.731 --> 02:40.289
Well, not quite.

02:40.466 --> 02:44.270
I'd like to introduce you to Kako Tatsumi.
She's a Japanese archery champion.

02:44.440 --> 02:46.101
She's gonna be helping us out today.

02:46.610 --> 02:49.479
And you have nothing to fear.
She placed sixth in Beijing.

02:52.252 --> 02:54.050
Are you joking?

02:54.222 --> 02:55.451
Is he...? Is he joking?

02:56.158 --> 02:58.822
Kalia, chin down, eyes here,
arms to your side.

03:00.298 --> 03:03.201
- Somebody tell me he's joking.
- Don't move.

03:03.370 --> 03:04.668
Kako, on my count.

03:08.278 --> 03:09.610
She didn't even medal!

03:14.821 --> 03:17.087
Just listen to my music.

03:19.328 --> 03:21.730
I am more than my look. I am.

03:21.900 --> 03:24.301
Sweetie, you are already gorgeous.

03:24.470 --> 03:27.237
Why do you need
to be good at two things, huh?

03:27.409 --> 03:28.933
Connor.

03:29.111 --> 03:31.638
- Need your select on the mayor's proofs.
- Now?

03:31.817 --> 03:33.718
And I'm juggling three of your buddies...

03:33.886 --> 03:35.821
...on iChat.
- Does she knock?

03:35.989 --> 03:39.222
Sorry. You told me to make sure
you were on the road by 2.

03:39.395 --> 03:40.555
Why?

03:40.729 --> 03:42.391
Your brother's wedding in Newport?

03:42.567 --> 03:44.799
- That's today?
- The rehearsal dinner's tonight...

03:44.971 --> 03:48.032
...at your Uncle Wayne's old estate.
- Oh, God, I gotta get up there.

03:48.209 --> 03:53.013
And I have Kiki, Charlece and Nadja
on your IM. They keep calling.

03:53.184 --> 03:56.382
- Nadja. Remind me who Nadja is again?
- Nadja was dinner Friday night.

03:56.555 --> 04:01.724
- Right. Very pretty girl. Didn't say much.
- She's Romanian. Barely speaks English.

04:01.897 --> 04:04.459
Well, that explains it.
Scan these to Mike right away.

04:04.635 --> 04:08.232
I am a touch busy, if you could
take care of those calls, I'd appreciate it.

04:08.407 --> 04:11.504
No. No way. I'm not breaking up with girls
for you, Connor.

04:11.680 --> 04:13.945
That's where I draw the line.
I believe in karma.

04:14.117 --> 04:15.551
Okay.

04:15.954 --> 04:17.786
- Conference them.
- Conference them?

04:17.957 --> 04:20.322
- Conference them.
- Oh, no, you wouldn't.

04:20.493 --> 04:22.360
Oh, yes, I would.

04:23.798 --> 04:25.927
They're conferenced.
Click here to disconnect.

04:26.436 --> 04:29.135
- Hello, ladies, it's Connor Mead.
- <i>Hi, Connor.</i>

04:29.308 --> 04:32.245
- <i>Hi.</i>
- <i>Whoa, is there anyone else on the line?</i>

04:32.414 --> 04:35.873
Listen, I'm sincerely pressed for time
right now, so I'm gonna...

04:36.053 --> 04:38.717
Well, I'm gonna have to do this in bulk.
Um...

04:39.492 --> 04:41.324
It's not gonna work out for us.

04:41.495 --> 04:43.087
- <i>Wait, are you kidding me?</i>
- <i>What?</i>

04:43.264 --> 04:46.029
<i>Tell me you're not breaking up</i>
<i>with me on a conference call.</i>

04:46.202 --> 04:49.174
- <i>But I thought things were going great.</i>
- <i>You are a womans hater.</i>

04:49.341 --> 04:50.673
<i>Connor Mead hates womans.</i>

04:50.843 --> 04:54.645
No, no, no, I love womans.
I mean, "women," all right?

04:54.816 --> 04:56.842
I love all women.
That's the problem here.

04:57.019 --> 05:00.890
<i>No. The problem is you date a girl for</i>
<i>two weeks, get her to fall in love with you</i>...

05:01.061 --> 05:05.624
<i>He takes the love and he hoard it,</i>
<i>like a miser.</i>

05:05.801 --> 05:08.999
Jesus, doesn't anyone
just wanna have fun anymore?

05:09.172 --> 05:10.197
I like to have fun.

05:10.374 --> 05:13.539
All right, then don't listen to these ladies.
They are crazy.

05:13.713 --> 05:16.377
<i>We can still hear you</i>
<i>when you cover the camera, you know.</i>

05:16.552 --> 05:18.487
- Right.
- <i>Emotionally retarded.</i>

05:18.654 --> 05:20.556
- <i>You really need therapy.</i>
- <i>You stupid boy.</i>

05:20.725 --> 05:23.629
Ladies, it sounds like you have
an awful lot to discuss, okay?

05:23.797 --> 05:27.359
So I'm gonna jump off,
but feel free to keep talking, okay?

05:27.535 --> 05:33.500
Kiki, Nadja, Charlece, I had an amazing time
with each one of you.

05:33.679 --> 05:35.614
I wish you all the best.

05:35.782 --> 05:37.945
- Goodbye.
- <i>No, we are not done</i>...

05:38.120 --> 05:40.681
You really are as bad as they say.

05:40.857 --> 05:44.352
Oh, no, dear, I am just a little bit worse.

05:44.530 --> 05:46.897
Of course, you'd never treat me
that way, right?

05:47.067 --> 05:51.131
No. I just did that for you.
I'm cleaning my plate for the main course.

05:52.542 --> 05:56.140
You're the biggest jerk ever.
In fact, you're even famous for it.

05:57.050 --> 05:59.418
No, really, why am I doing this?

05:59.587 --> 06:02.523
Well, it usually has something to do
with your father.

06:02.692 --> 06:05.664
Oh, please.
I've never even met my father.

06:06.633 --> 06:08.225
Well, come to papa.

07:02.121 --> 07:05.354
Okay, here we go.

07:05.827 --> 07:10.494
This will have gone like clockwork,
so at 1529 I will say:

07:10.668 --> 07:12.160
"You may kiss the bride."

07:12.338 --> 07:14.203
Oh, we should practice that,
shouldn't we?

07:15.576 --> 07:17.978
- Oh, God.
- Paulie. Hey.

07:18.147 --> 07:20.673
- Connor. Go around.
- Yeah.

07:20.851 --> 07:22.376
He came.

07:23.924 --> 07:25.949
- He came.
- He came.

07:26.126 --> 07:27.185
- What's wrong?
- What?

07:27.361 --> 07:30.423
Well, you and all but one of my bridesmaids
have slept with him...

07:30.600 --> 07:33.127
...so he can't be that bad, right?
- No.

07:33.305 --> 07:35.570
- Jenny, soothe the nervous bride.
- Oh, it's fine.

07:36.543 --> 07:38.512
Hey.

07:38.680 --> 07:40.582
Connor.

07:41.417 --> 07:43.444
- Good to see you. Yeah.
- You made it.

07:43.621 --> 07:45.089
- You look great.
- Thank you, man.

07:45.257 --> 07:48.194
What do you think about what
we did to Uncle Wayne's old karate dojo?

07:48.362 --> 07:49.990
- Whoa.
- I'm psyched.

07:50.166 --> 07:52.134
I didn't think
you were gonna make the rehearsal.

07:52.301 --> 07:53.964
Well, I wanted to get here early...

07:54.138 --> 07:57.075
...make sure you had time
to think about our last conversation.

07:57.245 --> 08:00.578
You know, the one about marriage, love,
never-ending lifelong monogamy?

08:00.749 --> 08:02.377
Yes, I definitely thought about it.

08:02.552 --> 08:04.076
- You did? Good, good.
- Yes, I did.

08:04.254 --> 08:07.124
If you're having second thoughts,
here's the key to my Jag.

08:07.293 --> 08:09.990
You give me the word, I'll block.

08:10.498 --> 08:12.695
- Oh, my God, you're serious.
- You're damn right.

08:12.869 --> 08:15.668
Man, I'll do anything for you.
Who's got your back, huh?

08:15.840 --> 08:19.301
Hey, it's you and me
against the world, right?

08:19.479 --> 08:21.141
Why is he giving him keys?

08:21.315 --> 08:24.115
- Why's he giving him keys?
- Oh, I bet he's giving you a car.

08:24.287 --> 08:26.813
- I'm just gonna go check on that.
- Okay.

08:26.991 --> 08:30.759
Connor, we've talked about this.
I wanna get married. I love Sandra.

08:30.931 --> 08:33.366
- You say that now, okay?
- Everything okay here, guys?

08:33.534 --> 08:35.767
Because we're still,
you know, rehearsing.

08:35.938 --> 08:37.966
- Jenny Perotti.
- Connor Mead.

08:38.143 --> 08:41.114
- I'll be damned.
- That's probably true.

08:41.280 --> 08:44.149
- Hey, the bride's unsupervised.
- I'm on it.

08:44.319 --> 08:47.518
- Buddy, we're not done talking about this.
- Done talking about what?

08:48.359 --> 08:50.624
- Options.
- Options.

08:50.797 --> 08:52.958
Yeah, listen to me, Connor.

08:53.133 --> 08:57.232
This is the biggest weekend in Sandy's life.
If you detract from her wedding...

08:57.407 --> 09:01.004
...I will sneak into your room
and cut off your favorite appendage.

09:01.180 --> 09:02.911
Now, the first part sounds nice.

09:03.084 --> 09:05.518
I can make it look like an accident.
Don't push me.

09:05.686 --> 09:09.853
Just try to be supportive. Normal.
Just not a train wreck for once.

09:10.027 --> 09:12.259
- I'll be on my best behavior.
- That worries me.

09:12.431 --> 09:14.422
I will, I'll be supportive. Whatever.

09:14.601 --> 09:15.967
- Really?
- Yes.

09:16.137 --> 09:17.366
Come on.

09:17.539 --> 09:20.304
See? I knew there wouldn't be
any weirdness between you two.

09:20.477 --> 09:24.645
- Connor, you remember Sandra?
- Yes, I do. How are you, Sandra?

09:25.486 --> 09:28.047
You know, it's not too late
to get out, gorgeous.

09:28.223 --> 09:29.486
He's joking.

09:29.659 --> 09:31.457
And you know the bridesmaids.

09:31.628 --> 09:34.998
Oh, yes, I do. Deena, Donna.
How are you?

09:35.168 --> 09:36.328
- And, uh...?
- Denice.

09:36.503 --> 09:39.065
- Nice to meet you, Denice. Ladies.
- Me too. How are you?

09:39.241 --> 09:42.076
My groomsmen.
Guys, this is my brother, Connor.

09:42.279 --> 09:44.248
- We've heard the stories, man.
- Oh, okay.

09:44.417 --> 09:47.478
- An honor to be serving with you.
- And with you.

09:47.653 --> 09:50.284
It's "mice" to "neet" you.
Damn it, I blew it.

09:50.459 --> 09:52.552
Sorry to break up the bromance,
guys, but...

09:52.729 --> 09:55.359
...I need you right here
where I can keep my eyes on you.

09:55.534 --> 09:58.060
- Absolutely.
- Are we ready?

09:58.237 --> 09:59.330
Yes, sorry, sarge.

09:59.841 --> 10:02.037
Sarge?
Are they getting married by a cop?

10:02.212 --> 10:05.410
Sergeant Major Volcom,
United States Marine Corps.

10:05.583 --> 10:08.384
I am not a cop.

10:09.856 --> 10:13.693
- Where'd you find this ray of sunshine?
- He's Sandra's dad.

10:13.863 --> 10:16.959
Sarge, this is my brother, Connor.
Connor, this is the sarge.

10:17.135 --> 10:19.128
He was ordained right after the war.

10:19.306 --> 10:22.675
Little war called Korea.
Perhaps you've heard of it, slick?

10:22.845 --> 10:24.677
Lost more men than Nam.

10:24.849 --> 10:27.216
We didn't get a wall.
We didn't get a movie.

10:27.385 --> 10:30.846
We got a sitcom with Alan Alda
which was all nonstop laughs...

10:31.024 --> 10:33.425
...unless you were the one
watching his friends die.

10:33.595 --> 10:36.122
The war's over, Dad. It was a tie.

10:36.299 --> 10:39.168
You know, we should probably try
to keep going on schedule.

10:39.338 --> 10:41.706
- Hua.
- Hua.

10:41.875 --> 10:45.939
Following the kiss at 1530 hours,
on my mark...

10:46.115 --> 10:48.084
...groom will take bride's left forearm...

10:48.252 --> 10:52.317
...rotate 180 degrees,
orienting north by northwest.

10:52.493 --> 10:55.360
Then I will announce you
as husband and wife.

10:55.530 --> 10:57.523
Following which...

10:59.302 --> 11:03.367
Following which,
you will live happily ever after.

11:05.547 --> 11:06.572
Oh, Daddy.

11:07.249 --> 11:09.582
- So sweet. Oh, my God.
- That is sweet.

11:10.721 --> 11:13.419
- I'm surrounded by huggers.
- There we go.

11:13.594 --> 11:16.529
- No, we're cool, man.
- Come on.

11:27.849 --> 11:31.287
Hey, Uncle Wayne.

11:34.260 --> 11:38.288
Ah, the world's a lot less fun
without you in it, buddy.

11:43.073 --> 11:45.407
Oh, no. Oh, no.

11:45.577 --> 11:49.071
No decorations in here. No.

11:49.250 --> 11:51.744
No. No.

11:51.922 --> 11:54.153
And, yes.

11:54.325 --> 11:55.350
No.

11:56.796 --> 12:01.166
- No! Wha...? What did...? What the...?
- Something wrong?

12:03.641 --> 12:06.133
I got over 30 scented candles
in my room.

12:06.311 --> 12:09.043
- Oh, the wedding scent is lavender.
- The wedding scent?

12:09.216 --> 12:12.153
- And people wonder why I'm not married.
- Not really.

12:12.321 --> 12:16.020
I mean, seriously, Jenny, my Uncle Wayne
is rolling over in his grave right now.

12:16.193 --> 12:18.163
No, come on. Wayne loved a good party.

12:18.331 --> 12:22.393
Party, yes. A wedding? No.
Back in the day that man used this place...

12:22.569 --> 12:27.100
...for mind-numbing, clothing-optional,
weeklong orgies, okay?

12:27.277 --> 12:29.577
Do you know Dean Martin
slept in that bathroom?

12:29.748 --> 12:32.878
He drank from the bidet
and sang the Canadian national anthem...

12:33.054 --> 12:34.352
...in Spanish.
- In Spanish.

12:34.523 --> 12:40.124
- Yeah, I remember Wayne telling us that.
- Yeah. Now that, that was a party. Not this.

12:42.103 --> 12:45.403
You know, people were taking bets
on whether or not you'd even show up.

12:45.574 --> 12:47.975
- Miss my kid brother's wedding?
- That's what I said.

12:48.144 --> 12:51.605
The whole asshole thing you do
is to get insecure women to sleep with you.

12:51.784 --> 12:55.620
- Deep down, you're a big sweetheart.
- Oh. Look who's got me pegged.

12:55.790 --> 12:59.593
And there's the sarcasm to cover up
the accidental display of affection for Paul.

12:59.764 --> 13:01.232
Hey.

13:02.068 --> 13:03.593
I'm not covering anything up.

13:04.337 --> 13:09.506
And I would also be more than happy to
take off the rest of my clothes to prove it.

13:09.680 --> 13:13.915
Then there's the cheap sexual innuendo.
All the old Connor Mead tricks are back.

13:14.087 --> 13:17.251
Well, don't worry,
your secret's safe with me.

13:17.426 --> 13:20.420
I won't tell anyone you have feelings.

13:22.634 --> 13:23.268
Hua!

13:23.268 --> 13:25.204
Hua!

13:27.641 --> 13:28.836
Oh, gosh.

13:29.010 --> 13:33.347
- Okay. Yeah, it didn't work. Still nervous.
- Let's do another one.

13:33.518 --> 13:36.922
- Sandy, what about him?
- Dan Palumbo. Married.

13:37.091 --> 13:38.490
Oh. Kids?

13:38.659 --> 13:40.959
What? They're not really married
unless they have kids.

13:41.130 --> 13:42.359
Hua.

13:42.534 --> 13:45.402
- Heard, understood, acknowledged.
- Sandy.

13:46.506 --> 13:48.497
Save some liquor
for the rest of the guests.

13:48.675 --> 13:50.736
- Bye, Mrs. Mead.
- Clean my room, pledge.

13:56.121 --> 13:58.591
Slow down. Slow down.

13:59.326 --> 14:00.487
- Hey.
- Here you are, sir.

14:00.662 --> 14:03.758
If you can keep those coming
all night. Thank you.

14:03.935 --> 14:05.835
And now we're off.

14:06.003 --> 14:07.369
- Excuse me, Mr. Mead?
- Mm-hm.

14:07.540 --> 14:09.873
I just wanna tell you,
I'm a huge fan of your work.

14:10.043 --> 14:12.775
- Thank you.
- Gonna photograph your brother's wedding?

14:13.248 --> 14:16.242
No. No, I'm not a wedding photographer.

14:16.420 --> 14:19.586
- Right, but it's your brother.
- Right.

14:19.759 --> 14:23.458
He's not good at taking pictures of people
with their clothes on.

14:23.632 --> 14:25.795
- Look who's funny.
- It's not his specialty.

14:27.171 --> 14:29.073
- Ah.
- Turn your phone off.

14:29.642 --> 14:30.940
Connor Mead.

14:31.411 --> 14:33.208
No, I would not like to cut my quota.

14:33.380 --> 14:35.680
- Connor.
- Look, just tell him to go screw himself.

14:35.851 --> 14:38.378
- Yeah, I said, tell him to go screw himself.
- Hey.

14:38.856 --> 14:41.850
Like when a man and a woman...
I gotta go. Gotta go.

14:42.029 --> 14:43.894
- Hi.
- Oh, my God.

14:44.064 --> 14:46.091
- Sit down before you...
- Oh, my God.

14:46.269 --> 14:47.932
